SaaSGrid is designed to support subscription or usage transaction based software revenue, and currently does not support revenue, such as hardware or services, or future Because SaaSGrid is focused on SaaS KPIs, the relevant revenue values may diverge from GAAP When filling out revenue in the SaaSGrid template, use the following guidelines: For subscription models, input Monthly Recurring Revenue (MRR) as of the end of each Some examples: A customer pays $1200 for a 1 year contract, starting in January: Input $100 for each month starting in A customer pays $1200 for a 1 year contract, starting in January, but in July pays an additional $600 to update their contract for the rest of the year: Input $100 per month for January - March, and $200 per month starting in A customer pays $10 per user per In January, they have 2 users halfway through February, they add 2 additional users: Input $20 for January and $40 for February, even if the amount the customer is charged for the month of February is <$40. In other words, ignore and use the end of monthÃ¢Â€Â™s For usage or transaction based models, input the net revenue accrued in the Some examples: A customer pays $1 per API call, and uses API calls in January: Input $500 for A customer pays $1 per API call and uses API calls in January, but their contract dictates they have a $750 month minimum: Input $750 for A customer pays 1% of their sales each In January, their sales are $50,000: Input $500 for The inputted revenue figure, regardless of whether it is MRR or net revenue, will be referred to as Ã¢Â€ÂœrevenueÃ¢Â€Â in the below KPI Ã¢Â€ÂœNew revenueÃ¢Â€Â will refer to the inputted revenue figure for customers who have never produced revenue in a previous Similarly, Ã¢Â€Âœnew customersÃ¢Â€Â are customers with inputted revenue in a given month and no revenue in any previous SaaSGrid is built for teams to Next Metric Sources Metric Sources are the inputs that SaaSGrid uses to calculate Currently, SaaSGrid supports Metric Sources uploaded by Brought to you by Craft Ã‚Â© SaaSGrid Product Growth Retention Economics Documentation Dashboard Company About Us Contact Blog Careers Legal User Agreement Privacy Policy   Blog | SaaSGrid Product DataÃ‚ Sync Dashboard Analysis Documentation Blog Log In Get Started The SaaSGrid Blog Release notes, updates, announcements, and 4 2022 We Launched Use at your own Risk As part of our most recent product launch we revamped our Ã¢Â€ÂœRetentionÃ¢Â€Â chart to show retention Read Now 4 2022 Can your company raise in a downturn? 7 8 2022 Accounting for Customer Success 7 28 2022 The SaaS Metrics That Matter Ready to see for yourself? In the last months of existence, Akto has raised a capital of $4.5M, became a team of members, served few of the largest alpha customers, and processed billion+ API We wrote our first line of code in November last year, and now have SaaS and versions running in production environments of customers across the Super looking forward to the exciting future What problem is Akto solving?Ã‚ Over million developers around the world use thousands of APIs These APIs carry sensitive data of users which if leaked can cause irreparable damage to Security teams struggle to secure these APIs because of: Ã¢Â€Â Lack of API inventory - If you are a developer or security engineer reading this, you can relate to this problem and probably have faced it in your own Agile and continuous release cycle movement has led to developers adding new APIs and updating existing ones very There is constant back and forth between developers and security engineers to get an updated API Over % of the companies we talked to face this Some of them have tried to solve this by creating a process around it - every time a developer creates an API or updates an API,Ã‚ he she will create an updated API documentation for Although this solves the problem butÃ‚ really slows down the development Ã¢Â€Â Hard to do business logic API security testing - Developers and security engineers donÃ¢Â€Â™t have a way to test their APIs for vulnerabilities before new ones are deployed in production or when existing ones are updated with new Most security engineers manually test a few important APIs before a release by writing their custom Some use tools such as Burp which require a lot of manual configuration to Now imagine doing this manually for a large number of APIs (1000s) and a large number of tests (50+) manually checking the results for false positives and following up with developers to remove the vulnerabilities Now imagine this is done before every release ( almost every week for most companies). Yes, itÃ¢Â€Â™s very very hard to do at scale for most To add to the problem, most of the difficult to detect vulnerabilities are business logic ones which are very hard to test for without Every company we talked to is struggling to solve these Moreover, most teams have to spend months and devops team bandwidth to integrate a tool of their choice as current tools are very hard to install and work " Ã¢Â€Â” How Akto solves this? Akto is the worldÃ¢Â€Â™s first plug and play API security Akto deploys in less than a minute to create an inventory of APIs, detects PII data leaks, misconfigurations and continuously tests these APIs for business logic flaws like broken authentication and authorization in CI CD We strongly believe in creating a continuous API inventory through API traffic with ZERO performance To do so, you can deploy Akto in your cloud ( AWS or GCP ), select load balancers to mirror your API traffic ( staging or production ) and thatÃ¢Â€Â™s Akto will now be able to generate a continuously updated API inventory for We are launching a very cool BURP extension this week using which you will be able to also mirror traffic through burp and load in Akto solves the testing problem through its robust API security testing module (in beta). Akto continuously learns API context through rich traffic data and uses that to reduce false positives in Once your API inventory is populated, you will be able to run automated business logic tests on all the APIs detected by Our customers Well, I cannot be more thankful to our early customers who have supported us in every way possible to make a great Thanks for believing in us, being patient with the building and solving for We promise to keep you happy with our Some of the largest companies around the world are using Akto to discover and test their Akto has discovered more than ,000 APIs and detected + auth vulnerabilities for its What we did in last months? Ã¢Â€Â Our first 5 months: were about building our product for scale which required real production We thank each of our first five customers, who believed in two people without any company existence, used our product and gave continuous Within six months, Akto was able to handle requests a day (Google-scale traffic).
